Task 3: Using AVR language, implement a counter that increments
a single register by 1 every 1 second. Identify the number of CPU
cycles and instructions that that place within this window for your
code. Implement a serial command that allows you to store or
reset the current counter value in the EEPROM. Unplug Arduino.
On power-up, the counter should continue from the last stored
value rather than starting over (unless reset).
Explain any anomalies or limitations that may occur. Indicate the
address location of the register you are using to increment a
value.

